**Tests:** (Tier 1 / high-stakes: shells out + does FS materialization;
behavior REPRODUCED, not asserted from memory.)
- input materialization writes <ScratchDir>/inputs/<NN>-<role> with right
  bytes + index padding (verify on disk, multiple inputs incl. index >= 10).
- command runs with cwd=WorktreeDir: fake script reads a cwd-relative marker
  file and folds it into output (proves cwd).
- command sees ETUDE_INPUTS_DIR/ETUDE_OUTPUT_FILE: fake script reads an input
  via the env var and writes via the env var; output read back into RunResult.
- non-zero exit -> ErrRunnerFailed; error string contains trimmed stderr + exit status.
- exit 0 but no output file -> ErrOutputMissing.
- MediaType default: runner leaves it empty -> result gets req.OutputMediaType
  (asserts applyResultDefaults wiring); output is file bytes only so the default
  always applies.
- RunResult.Producer == req.Producer (full producer echo: Harness/Model/Skill all
  carried through unchanged), asserting the post-1.3 seam.
- validation: empty Command -> ErrRunnerNotConfigured; relative/missing
  WorktreeDir or ScratchDir -> invalid-dir error; ScratchDir inside WorktreeDir
  -> rejected (incl. the prefix-trap sibling /wt-other is ACCEPTED).
- real t.TempDir() for ScratchDir + a separate fake worktree dir (sibling).
- skip on Windows or guard script tests with sh availability (build a tiny
  helper that writes an executable sh script; runtime.GOOS guard).

**Docs:** None yet. No CLI/user-facing surface lands in this bead (ExecRunner is
internal wiring); the replay command + its docs are the next bead
(etude-replay-command). The I/O + env-var contract is documented in code
(doc comments on ExecRunner / Run) so etude-replay-command can rely on it.
Confirmed: no user docs to update here.

**Risks:**
- Exec env-var contract is provisional — the real claude/Agent-SDK adapter may
  need richer signalling (multiple outputs, structured result). Mitigation:
  single output file + env vars is the minimal reproduced contract; documented
  as the v1 contract; RunResult.Producer override (discovered skill version/model)
  is a future hook, echo req.Producer for now.
- Cross-platform: sh-script tests are POSIX. Mitigation: guard with runtime.GOOS
  and write the script via os.WriteFile + chmod (no shell invocation in prod code).
- Otherwise low — mirrors two established, tested exec call sites.

